      • updateCheckout

        CancellableTask updateCheckout(Checkout checkout,
                               Callback<Checkout> callback)
        Update an existing Checkout's attributes. Only the following attributes will be updated, any others will be ignored:
        • Checkout.email
        • Checkout.shippingAddress
        • Checkout.billingAddress
        • Checkout.lineItems
        • Checkout.discount
        • Checkout.shippingRate
        • Checkout.reservationTime
        Parameters:
        checkout - the Checkout attributes to be updated, not null
        callback - the Callback that will be used to indicate the response from the asynchronous network operation, not null
        Returns:
        cancelable task

      • updateCheckout

        rx.Observable<Checkout> updateCheckout(Checkout checkout)
        Update an existing Checkout's attributes Only the following attributes will be updated, any others will be ignored:
        • Checkout.email
        • Checkout.shippingAddress
        • Checkout.billingAddress
        • Checkout.lineItems
        • Checkout.discount
        • Checkout.shippingRate
        • Checkout.reservationTime
        Parameters:
        checkout - the Checkout to update, not null
        Returns:
        cold observable that emits updated checkout object

      • getCheckoutCompletionStatus

        CancellableTask getCheckoutCompletionStatus(String checkoutToken,
                                            Callback<Boolean> callback)
        Get the status of the payment session associated with checkout. callback will be called with a boolean value indicating whether the session has completed or not.
        Parameters:
        checkoutToken - checkout token for the Checkout to get the completion status for, not null or empty
        callback - the Callback that will be used to indicate the response from the asynchronous network operation, not null
        Returns:
        cancellable task

      • removeProductReservationsFromCheckout

        CancellableTask removeProductReservationsFromCheckout(String checkoutToken,
                                                      Callback<Checkout> callback)
        Release all product inventory reservations associated with the checkout by setting the `reservationTime` of the checkout to `0` and calling updateCheckout(Checkout, Callback). We recommend creating a new `Checkout` object from a `Cart` for further API calls.
        Parameters:
        checkoutToken - the token for the Checkout to expire, not null or empty
        callback - the Callback that will be used to indicate the response from the asynchronous network operation, not null
        Returns:
        cancelable task

      • removeProductReservationsFromCheckout

        rx.Observable<Checkout> removeProductReservationsFromCheckout(String checkoutToken)
        Release all product inventory reservations associated with the checkout by setting the `reservationTime` of the checkout to `0` and calling updateCheckout(Checkout, Callback). We recommend creating a new `Checkout` object from a `Cart` for further API calls.
        Parameters:
        checkoutToken - the Checkout to expire, not null or empty
        Returns:
        cold observable that emits updated checkout
